Text.val: Always check if the counterparty RE_ID has changed. If so, the template mus be recreated
Subject To VAT ratio must be greater than zero or else no charges subject to vat can be present:
Subject To VAT ratio must be less than one or else no charges NOT subject to vat can be present:
Still differences found then correct these differences on the 'Not Subject To Vat' part and the invoice amount.
Exceptions appear when the subjectToVatRatio = 1 (= 100% subject to VAT). In that case there will be no 'Not subject to vat'
part, so the correction will be done on the 'Subject to vat' part. Also when the max amount is bigger than the invoice amount
no correction of the difference can be done since it wil alway result in an invoice amount bigger than the max amount.
Prevent the invoice amount from being bigger than the max amount. This would be caused by the increasing VAT amount.

SQL_STMT_U.val: SELECT cr.cfcu_id FROM contextcalculationrules co inner join transactiesoorten t ON t.ts_indicatie_nummer = co.cxcr_ts_indicatienummer inner join calculationrules cr ON cr.cfcu_id = co.cxcr_cfcu_id inner join deduction_definition dd ON dd.id=cr.cfcu_dedu_id inner join mutationcodes_per_calcrule mc ON mc.cfcu_id = cr.cfcu_id inner join mutationcodes m ON m.id=mc.mutationcode_id where co.cxcr_context='COSTFEES' and t.ts_symbool='O-G' and dd.report_code='SERVICEFEE' and m.code=~1
